<br>
But even to such a soul, the prospect of going through all the motions of practicing in addition to doing the actual research can be daunting to say the least.<br>
<br>
At level 24 I found myself at the point where the issue could not be postponed any further. <br>
I got an overview of the materials needed and got the practice tome from the gypsy by trading away my beloved greater lightstone which I was fortunate to have by coincidence from before. <br>
I had the recipes from somewhere in these boards that claimed to be nearly 100% correct and not without expectation I made an attempt to make my very first azla practice rune. It failed. Obviously the very first recipe of the very first practice rune was false.<br>
I sat back and started to sweat.<br>
I was afraid I maybe had to run all the way back to the gypsies from my beloved Ak'Anon to get the recipe books, but I wasn't gonna give up that easy.<br>
So I did a /who using magician filter and started to tell the first few high level mages I could find to politely ask if they knew the recipes for the first few practice runes. <br>
After having talked to many a friendly mage ranging from 30 to some 40 levels, the conclusion could not be more unanimous.<br>
None of them knew anything about practice research because none of them had ever had any use for it.<br>
What they all had done was simply to pour the maximum number of practice points into the research skill at their guild trainers and started researching.<br>
Luckily I have always been extremely stingy with my practice points and had over 80 of them left myself.<br>
I saw a way to get out of the would be extremely time consuming and maybe even class discouraging process of research practice and went ahead and poured the max allowed points into my research skill. The very first research I attempted was everfount and I was successful at my first try.<br>
<br>
I don't think I will ever practice research except through the actual researching itself, and boy am I glad!<br>
<br>
Snifnix lvl 25 gnome mage Mith Marr. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uezno.showPublicProfile>Ezno</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(3/9/00 10:00:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Practice research. Newbies check this out!</span><hr size=1> <br>
